cases.title: Measure Netskope Transit Time (By Sniffer)
cases.custom_summary: Measure Netskope Transit Time (By Sniffer)
cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a Sniffer at NSproxy
2. Send a imitaion HTTP Request from Client to www.box.com
3. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while recieving from Client (HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME)
3. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while sending from NSproxy (HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT)
4. Request_Transit_Time should be HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT - HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME
5. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while receiving from box.com (HTTP_RES_HDR)
6. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while sending from NSproxy (HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT)
7. Response_Transit_Time should be HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT - HTTP_RES_HDR
8. X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time
cases.custom_expected: X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time

1. Start a Sniffer at NSproxy
2. Send a imitaion TCP SYN packet from Client to www.box.com
3. Copy the timestamp of TCP SYN while recieving from Client (TCP_SYN)
4. Copy the timestamp of TCP ACK while fowarding from NSproxy (TCP_ACK)
5. X-NS-TCP-CONN-TIME should be TCP_ACK - TCP_SYN
cases.custom_expected: X-NS-TCP-CONN-TIME should be TCP_ACK - TCP_SYN

cases.title: Using GRE as ACM to Measure Transmit Time
cases.custom_summary: Using GRE as ACM to Measure Transmit Time
cases.custom_steps:
1. Start a watson log level synthetic to 5 at NSproxy
2. Setup GRE tunneling from GRE agent to Proxy
3. Send a imitaion SSL Client Hello packet from Client to www.box.com
4. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME)
5. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop req transit time: " (HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT)
6. Request_Transit_Time should be HTTP_REQ_HDR_SENT - HTTP_REQ_HDR_RESUME
7. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "start resp transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR)
8. Copy the timestamp of HTTP Request while seeing the log "stop ns transit time: " (HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT)
9. Response_Transit_Time should be HTTP_RES_HDR_SENT - HTTP_RES_HDR
10. X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time
cases.custom_expected: X-NS-TRANSIT-TIME should be Request_Transit_Time + Response_Transit_Time

Ref: ENG-483970, QE-43924
cases.custom_steps:
1. Create url list with *.Example.com and Example.com
2. Create custom category with all predefined categories and excluded url list.
3. Create web access block policy with category
4. Access url (http://Example.com ) of excluded category
cases.custom_expected:
Access to http://example.com  is ok
Access url (http://Example.com ) of excluded category will not get blocked and not generate alert.

2. Enable log levels tcp trans_event 1 user 3 httpmod httpreq 4 httpauth 5 
3. Generate traffic ( please use a simple GET if possible so we can search the log consistently)
4. (optional) authentication steps
5. Collect transaction events
6. Compared with expected results
7. Collect the log (please separate log for every access method )

Eg: ISSUE DETECTED: Mismatched authentication

cases.title: Verify the Transaction Event with IPSEC/GRE + NsClient passive mode
cases.custom_summary: Verify the Transaction Event with IPSEC/GRE + NsClient passive mode
cases.custom_steps:
1. Set feature flag to disabled. The lookup will be skip.
2. Set steering configuration as traffic type: all (On-prem)
3. Set a source location bypassed in exception for on-prem
4. Not set the same source location bypassed in exception for off-prem (all web traffic)
5. Send traffic from that specific source location
6. Check log. The traffic should NOT be bypassed. Since the Lookup will be skip
cases.custom_expected: Traffic will NOT be bypassed
